{{Infobox book | <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Novels or Wikipedia:WikiProject_Books --> | image = FiveStories.jpg | image_size = 200px | caption = 1956 p/b edition | name = Five Stories | author = [[Willa Cather]] | country = United States | language = English | genre = ([[historical fiction]]) | publisher = [[Vintage Books]] | release_date = 1956 | pages = 214 }}
'''''Five Stories''''' is a collection of stories, published in 1956<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.kirjasto.sci.fi/wcather.htm |title=Willa Siebert Cather |website=Books and Writers ''(kirjasto.sci.fi)'' |first=Petri |last=Liukkonen |publisher=[[Kuusankoski]] Public Library |location=Finland |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110116075657/http://kirjasto.sci.fi/wcather.htm |archivedate=16 January 2011 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref> by the Estate of [[Willa Cather]], after the author's death. Several of these stories had been previously published in other collections.
==Contents== This collection contains the following stories:<ref>Table of contents, Vintage Books reprint, 1979</ref> * "[[The Enchanted Bluff]]" * "[[Tom Outland's Story]]" * "[[Neighbour Rosicky]]" * "[[The Best Years]]" * "[[Paul's Case]]" * Unfinished Avignon Story: An Article by George N. Kates
