[[File:The_Perfect_Accord_LACMA_AC1999.18.1.jpg|thumb|300px]]
'''''Perfect Harmony''''' or '''''Perfect Accord''''' (French - ''L'Accord parfait'') is a 1719 painting by [[Antoine Watteau]], now in the [[Los Angeles County Museum of Art]]. It was the pendant to the same artist's ''[[The Surprise (painting)|The Surprise]]''.

It was initially owned by a friend of the artist, [[Nicolas d'Hénin de Cuvillers|Nicolas Hénin]], but it and ''Surprise'' were sold separately by his heir around 1756.

